This gene may play a role in acetylcholine metabolism.
Human CUTA wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 6p21.32 and is approximately 2 kb in length. This allele, which encodes protein CutA, may be involved in acetylcholinesterase localization.
Protein CutA (179 aa, ~19 kDa) is encoded by the human CUTA gene. This protein may play a role in acetylcholinesterase activity.
A rare endometrial carcinoma characterized by the presence of both malignant glandular and malignant squamous cellular components.
This gene is involved in endoplasmic reticulum-to-Golgi protein transport and tumor induction of immune responses.

Human CTAGE5 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 14q13.3 and is approximately 122 kb in length. This allele, which encodes endoplasmic reticulum export factor CTAGE5 protein, plays a role in the protein transport and induction of the immune response.
Endoplasmic reticulum export factor CTAGE5 (804 aa, ~91 kDa) is encoded by the human CTAGE5 gene. This protein is involved in intracellular protein transport and tumor induced immune responses.
This gene plays a role in ciliogenesis.

Human BBS9 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 7p14 and is approximately 477 kb in length. This allele, which encodes protein PTHB1, is involved in ciliogenesis. Mutation of both copies of this gene is associated with Bardet-Biedl syndrome 9.
Protein PTHB1 (887 aa, ~99 kDa) is encoded by the human BBS9 gene. This protein plays a role in cilium formation.
This gene is involved in phospholipid transport.

Human ATP8B2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1q21.3 and is approximately 26 kb in length. This allele, which encodes probable phospholipid-transporting ATPase ID protein, plays a role in aminophospholipid translocation.
Phospholipid-transporting ATPase ID (1209 aa, ~137 kDa) is encoded by the human ATP8B2 gene. This protein is involved in the translocation of aminophospholipids.
Inflammation of the bladder resulting in bloody urine.
The presence of a calculus in the pelvis of the kidney; this is most often composed of mineral salts and proteins.
A question about whether an individual feels or has felt that they are slowed down.

value.value: A question about whether an individual feels or has felt frightened, like butterflies in the stomach.
A question about whether an individual feels or has felt that they have lost interest in their appearance.
A question about whether an individual feels or has felt restless.
This gene plays a role in autophagy.

Human ATG4C wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p31.3 and is approximately 81 kb in length. This allele, which encodes cysteine protease ATG4C protein, is involved in proteolysis during autophagy.
A question about whether an individual looks forward to things with enjoyment.
Cysteine protease ATG4C (458 aa, ~52 kDa) is encoded by the human ATG4C gene. This protein plays a role in proteolysis of autophagy-regulatory proteins.
A question about whether an individual feels or has felt sudden feelings of panic.

label.value: Can Enjoy a Book, Radio, or TV Program

value.value: A question about whether an individual feels or has felt that they can enjoy a book, radio, or TV program.
A response indicating that something happens or happened a lot of the time.
A response indicating a certainty that something occurs with the same frequency or intensity as previously.
A response indicating that something occurs with a bit less frequency or intensity as previously.
This gene may be involved in vesicle trafficking.
Human ARFIP1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 4q31.3 and is approximately 139 kb in length. This allele, which encodes arfaptin-1 protein, may play a role in vesicular transport.
Arfaptin-1 (373 aa, ~42 kDa) is encoded by the human ARFIP1 gene. This protein may be involved in intracellular vesicle trafficking.
A response indicating that something occurs with little frequency or intensity.
A response indicating that something occurs rarely or with very little intensity.
A response indicating a certainty that something occurs with high intensity.
This gene plays a role in phospholipid metabolism.
Stone(s) within the urinary tract.

Human AGPAT5 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 8p23.1 and is approximately 53 kb in length. This allele, which encodes 1-acyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate acyltransferase epsilon protein, is involved in lysophosphatidic acid metabolism.

1-acyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate acyltransferase epsilon (364 aa, ~42 kDa) is encoded by the human AGPAT5 gene. This protein plays a role in the synthesis of phosphatidic acid from lysophosphatidic acid.
This gene is involved in both cation transport and membrane potential.
A response indicating that something occurs with moderate intensity.

Human ASIC2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17q12 and is approximately 1162 kb in length. This allele, which encodes acid-sensing ion channel 2 protein, plays a role in the modulation of membrane potential through proton-gated cation transport.

label.value: A Little, But it Doesn't Worry Me

value.value: A response indicating that something occurs, but causes little concern.
